sequenceDiagram
    participant User as User / Job Controller
    participant K8sAPI as Kubernetes API Server<br/>443/TCP HTTPS TLS 1.2+
    participant Webhook as Kueue Webhook Server<br/>9443/TCP HTTPS TLS
    participant Controller as Kueue Controller Manager
    participant Scheduler as Kueue Scheduler<br/>(in-process goroutine)
    participant Cache as In-Memory Cache /<br/>Queue Manager
    participant Prometheus as Prometheus<br/>8443/TCP HTTPS TLS
    participant WorkerK8s as Worker Cluster API<br/>443/TCP HTTPS TLS 1.2+

    Note over User,Cache: Flow 1: Job Submission and Admission

    User->>K8sAPI: POST Job/PyTorchJob/RayJob CR<br/>Auth: ServiceAccount/User token
    K8sAPI->>Webhook: POST /mutate-*<br/>TLS, API Server client cert
    Webhook-->>K8sAPI: Mutated (suspend=true,<br/>queue-name label added)
    K8sAPI->>Webhook: POST /validate-*<br/>TLS, API Server client cert
    Webhook-->>K8sAPI: Validated (quota, labels, specs)
    K8sAPI-->>User: Job CR created (suspended)

    Note over Controller,Cache: Controller watches Job CR, creates Workload

    Controller->>K8sAPI: Watch: Job CR change detected<br/>Auth: ServiceAccount token
    Controller->>K8sAPI: CREATE Workload CR<br/>(pod sets, resource requests, priority)
    K8sAPI-->>Controller: Workload CR created

    Controller->>Cache: Enqueue Workload<br/>(in-process Go channels)

    Note over Scheduler,Cache: Scheduler evaluates pending Workloads

    Scheduler->>Cache: Pull pending Workloads
    Cache-->>Scheduler: Workload list with requirements
    Scheduler->>Scheduler: Evaluate ClusterQueue quotas,<br/>flavor matching, preemption,<br/>fair sharing, TAS

    alt Admission Granted
        Scheduler->>Controller: Admit Workload<br/>(assigned ClusterQueue, flavors)
        Controller->>K8sAPI: PATCH Workload status=Admitted<br/>Auth: ServiceAccount token
        Controller->>K8sAPI: PATCH Job suspend=false<br/>(unsuspend the job)
        K8sAPI-->>Controller: Job running
    else Quota Insufficient - Preemption
        Scheduler->>Controller: Preempt lower-priority Workloads
        Controller->>K8sAPI: PATCH target Workload<br/>eviction annotation
        Controller->>K8sAPI: PATCH target Job suspend=true
        Scheduler->>Controller: Re-admit original Workload
    end

    Note over Prometheus,Controller: Flow 2: Metrics Collection

    Prometheus->>Controller: GET /metrics<br/>8443/TCP HTTPS TLS<br/>Auth: Bearer Token (SA token)
    Controller->>K8sAPI: TokenReview + SubjectAccessReview<br/>Auth: ServiceAccount token
    K8sAPI-->>Controller: Auth verified
    Controller-->>Prometheus: Metrics response<br/>(admission, queue, workload metrics)

    Note over Controller,WorkerK8s: Flow 3: MultiKueue Workload Distribution (Optional)

    Controller->>K8sAPI: Watch MultiKueueConfig,<br/>MultiKueueCluster CRs
    K8sAPI-->>Controller: MultiKueue config
    Controller->>WorkerK8s: CREATE remote Workload + Job<br/>Auth: kubeconfig from Secret
    WorkerK8s-->>Controller: Remote Workload status
    Controller->>K8sAPI: PATCH local Workload status<br/>(sync remote admission/completion)
